\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 
Oh - oh the - the coffin - coffin always came to your house then, there was none of the - none of this - lying in over night or anything. It - it was just in the house. There had to be a - a bedroom cleared, well the bedroom was cleared
. You know, to leave a - a - a room for nothing but the coffin, see. And they - they did this of course. That was all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 How was it taken from the house to the church?
