Well - it - it was the near - just walk, it was just a walking funeral. It was 
just a hearse of course, the hearse was - the hearse was in - hearse took the - the body. But the men just walked - walked at the end of the - these two - some of - two or three, the likes of the head - the head ones, like his son and that and the grandso
n. I was one of the - them that was walking at the side you see, the sort of the head ones walked - four on each side. See, of the coach, and then the less fell in behind.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Was it a horsedrawn hearse?
