Was we taken out? No. No, no, no. You - you see - I were always - the - the whole thing was - families were always so big, large families, I 
wouldna say big, large families them days. They'd all sufficient to do themselves without talking anyone else's family out, you understand what I mean. But there was always an uncle or an aunt knocking around when they married - that would take you out. W
e
 were really lucky in that - in that respect, that we'd - two aunts - at one - at one time would take us, another one you know. We was lucky in that respect, that they could come and give you a birthday and - and - this sort of thing, you know, they were 
handy that way.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Would they take you visiting?
