Ahy? Well - yes. I can remember one very vividly. It was - why I remember it so vividly - is - will come out in the
 story. We were going down to Rothesay. Well - it was - there was dad and I, you see, and mother, that was like three. Well there was twelve in the end, so there must have been nine - other nine children, we were going to - were going down to Rothesay. So
 you went down to the Grimaloch and you'd got to go to Grimaloch - you don't know where the Grimaloch is, no, well it's the top of the play. It's good enough for that you know, the the Grima}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8212307\charrsid8538783 loch, everything left from the G}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 rimaloch - to Rothesay. Sailing - s
ailing all the way, all right down the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Clyde{\*\xmlclose}
. See? So - thing was this, and a big crowd like that, you see, they'd all to be paid for. It wasnae very much - it wasnae very much but they still had to be paid for. Well the thing was, whenever you got on the 
boat and it was sailing down - and it was just ready to go off, you see, the children all knew. We - that's like I was one of the children. We all knew, this is happening in all the families that was there, you scattered, all over the boat, so it just lef
t mother and dad you see, and maybe - maybe - a youngster or something that my mother's had that was too young to - knock around on its own. That was to skirt the conductor who was going round to see about the fares. Oh }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8212307\charrsid8538783 that}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783  was - that was a regular thing, 
aye. Then you had a band, you'd a band playing on the boat then too, oh - it was quite handy. And when you got to Rothesay you wouldna know nothing about this, a lot of people nowadays don't know anything about it, when you got to Rothersay - there was al
l
 port - porters waiting on the boat coming in, big - big luggage. And - they had a peculiar way of drawing your attention then. When you were coming off the boat they - they just - pointed at you as you're coming off. But you would think that was for anot
h
er purpose altogether. That was to see if you'd any luggage - to carry off. And they called these porters the pointing - porters. The pointing - porters. You got it? That went on for quite a long time. Oh a number of years, aye, that's what they called th
em, the pointing porters, in Rothesay, everyone knew a pointing porter at Rothesay.
