Oh you did - went there for the day, oh yes, oh aye. Well you only - you only played rough. You see, you'd maybe go off and - of c
ourse the mother and maybe three or four rolls cut up and sandwiches and - and that you see and you get a - a bottle of - brown rum, that - was - the ginger beer at night and - brown rum they called it at that time, that would mean a - favourite drink. An
d
 then you - the - like of the father and mother, they were the toffs you see, they would have pies. We others had to be - had to be done with - with ham in it you know and - and made up in a right - wee - wee sandwiches. But - I say wee sandwiches, big sa
n
dwiches, you know, with bread about that thick with thick butter on it and then - a slice of ham or - or - or - or gammon or - you know, some - something in that line, cheese and - all that sort of stuff, aye. Oh aye. Oh you'd bring a bit out and - and - 
you got an odd bottle of - as I say, brown rum, that was our ginger, we just say ginger, that's easier said, just ginger.
