ou could - there was plenty of sand, oh wasnae plenty of sand, no, there's no - there's no too much sand at Rothesay. But there was as much as like you - could play around, and then - and then - there was - a good long beach where you - you - you'd races 
a
nd - and - the usual fun that the youngsters had you know. Did dyke - dykies - dyking, the sort of game that you - you - you'd to jump over one - two, three, four, you know. And - and there was - the idea was that they'd to try and knock you off, while yo
u
're on. You understand me, you know the - you - you know this girl of twenty, all in a row, down like this, you understand, and you - like just like leap frog. And you'd to jump - over, and while you're jumping over they - whoever you're jumping over has 
t
o try and knock you off. You see, and if he - he knocked you off he just - he's got to get at the back now, you've got to stand bending over. Well that's partly - some of the - of course you'd always a football, you know, a ball with you or something to p
lay football or rounders. You - you know what rounders is? Ah well, you know rounder, well play rounders too. Anything you could play with a ball, then it's skipping ropes. Oh aye, we played all these games.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Did your mother and dad join in?
