ending on your - pocket money from your uncles and aunts. And the olders and that. As we mostly did, penny in your pocket money. You'd get a hapenny here and ha'penny there and a farthing there and a - a - then you see you'd - two or three coppers and if 
y
ou had any more than threepence - my mum was standing there with the - what was over threepence. She - she wanted her - she wanted her quarter. Things was tight you know, you - you - you don't really understand how tight it was, there was nothing to spare
