\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 How much did they see of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 They - how much did they what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 How much did they see of them? How often did they used to meet them?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Well - they - they used to - when - when we were in 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Glasgow{\*\xmlclose} - when we were in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Glasgow{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 now - there used to be one relative came every - Saturday night, from Kilburnie. And what they came to 
Glasgow for was to go to the - to the - hall, the Bethany Hall, or the Burdette Hall rather it was, Burdette Hall on a Sunday morning, to feed the - down and outs and in Glasgow. Give them their breakfast. And that's what they came to - away from Kilburni
e
 - to give - they stayed with us on a Saturday night. Just slept on the floor because there wasnae a bed for him. Slept on the floor, and I say he came - he came there every Saturday so you know that - that was one person you would say was doing a pretty 
good turn. And - putting himself to a lot of inconvenience to do it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 
Whereabouts would your parents meet your relatives, would they go to their houses? If they were going to see your aunts and uncles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Oh they had to go to their houses if they wan
ted to see them, there were no other way of seeing them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8212307\charrsid8538783 Would your relatives come and visit you?}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 
Oh yes. Och aye, you - they wandered out and in all the time, you never knew who was in your house. Oh aye. Sometimes you'd have nobody and another
 day half a dozen there. But you see, they no - you never turned away from any house. Oh no. If - if - if you - well we'll say - you - you're talking about rel - relatives, we'll say that - a - a - an uncle and aunt came to see you now. And there was no r
o
om for them, well - everything was occupied, that was all. A bed in this dining room. You just pulled a bit of - one of the best that was there already, put that down on the floor, put some blankets and pillow and that was in for the night. A bed on the f
loor. That's what they done.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Did your parents have friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 
Friends? Oh all friends, aye, there was - people were all friendly at that time, everybody. Oh aye, there were no - everybody was your friend, any house you went into - in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}
Glasgow{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} too, there were no - no just differentiating between the two. In {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Glasgow{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} too, any house you went into was your pal.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 
Where would your parents see their friends? Just visiting at each others houses?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Oh that's - you see they went in the houses because - 
as I tell you, if - if you went in anyone's house - in Glasgow even, this - this - this is the early period mark you, you knocked at the door, nobody's - oh - just come in. Didn't ask you what you wanted or anything, just come in, sit down. Oh the caper t
hat went on first thing you know. You - you, you and you, go on, out. That's when they were telling their wee stories. You didna get listening in, oh no. Oh no. We wanted to listen in but we never got to hear anything, no, you'd to go out.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Did your parents share the same friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Share the same bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 
Oh yes, och they were all - as I tell you they were all friendly, everybody was your friend.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Did your mother have friends of her own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Not - oh no, there were nothing - t
here were nothing like that, no. If - ever she was friends, was my friends. Oh aye, share and share alike you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 What about your father, did he have special friends of his own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Well - the only time he had any special friends is when he was aw
ay at these trade union meetings. That was the only time he had any - other times he was - he's just knocking about the house, he wouldn't be knocking about - he was working about the house, wasnae time to knock about the house, you see. Working, or else 
he was away at some meeting or something. Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Can you remember were your parents friends invited into your house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 
My parents friends? Friends - were invited in? I wouldna - I wouldna have said any such thing as inviting them I'm telling you. T
hey just turned up, walked in, they were sure of a bed and they were sure of a meal. Oh aye, there were no - no such thing as these - these invitations going out. Oh no, you - you knew you were all right when you landed at - your hotel.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 What about particular days or occasions?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Holidays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 The holiday or Sundays or Christmas, would friends be invited then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 
No. No, no, the - the - that was the rule - if - if - if a door - if - if - if they were at home, you were at home. That was the idea 
- all over. That carried right throughout Scotland, I don't know about England, but that was right through Scotland. Didna matter where you went, supposing you went away up to Oban or - it was all the same. When you went into a house you were at home.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Did that apply to neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 
That applied to neighbours, yes. The neighbours just run out and in each others houses. Some parts of Glasgow they do that yet, the key - you'll see the key in the door, maybe you'll never see it, but - you see the key 
in the door, you just turn the key and walk in. Make yourself a cup of tea if - if there's nobody there.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 People often tell us that in those days everybody made their own amusements.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Yes. Mostly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 What do you think your parents did when they got together with their friends?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 
What did they do? Oh - all - all they did was cutting each other to ribbons. Oh I don't know - I don't know what they would do because we never knew at all, you - you - you - you were out. Out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Did they ever go and make music anywhere?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 
Well, they - the - the dad had a flute and there was all the men nearly had flutes. And then a flute band, you know what a flute is, you know the - aye, that - that's the only kind of music ever I knew them to have.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 What about games would they play cards or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 
Oh they would play cards, och aye, and then - they - they - they'd kites, they played kites - the kiting in the summertime. You - you know what kites are don't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 That's the little round things that you throw?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Aye, they throw onto the clay thing, aye. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Would that be the men who would do that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 
That was the men. Oh aye, the women didna play that game, no, that's too strenuous for the women, that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Did the women play cards?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 
No. That - that's not nice in - that's not nice in those Scotch girls, oh no. Oh no, no. That's - that's bad mans cards.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 
Many people divide society into different social classes or groups. In that time when you were a child did you think of some people as belonging to one and some to another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 
But - in the - you mean - everyone gathering in - Protestants, is that what you mean. You mean - church people, different denominations.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 No, things like upper class and working class, those sort of differences.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 
No, no, no, no, the only - the only man - the only people - people in the village in the village, I mean, now you count the village - I'm counting the - villages in Glasgow here too, the little communes you know. No, no, the 
only two persons that were recognized above the common realm, is the minister - and the doctor. It didnae matter how much money somebody else had, they just - they just weren't there. They - they weren't considered class. You see, doctor - the doctor was 
considered class, and the minister. Outside of those two the rest of them - money wasne - nothing at all and - didnae make 'em class.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 What about people with very low incomes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 With very low incomes? Well it's all incomes at that time, but there - 
there was people with very low incomes, well - what - what was done really - was - as far as I remember, this is - this is - is - as I'm saying, I'm back at my own house again you understand, I'm not saying the general thing, this might not be general. Wa
s
 the likes of - in our family now - well that's like - I'm saying our family, but that's all the relatives attached to our family you see, our uncles and aunts and aunts and aunts and aunts, and maybe a hundred of them altogether. And - in different state
s
. Well if there was any one of those - needing an-thing, they got it. They just subscribed right away. They didna make any - did - didna make the feel poor house or anything about it. It was just they saw and they would - say I think that - I think Johnni
e needs a pair of trousers, do you no think so? Aye what's his size now? Aye, well, next time we're up in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Glasgow{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
, get him a pair of trousers. Bought it down and - and they just - left it down there, that was it, they didnae - he - he knew they'd left it but that was all there was to it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Which class would you say you belonged to yourself, your own family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 The working class. Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 What sort of families belonged to the same class as you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Well - as I'm telling you - the - the only - the onl
y people that was con - be considered above - we'll say - they working class is I'm saying - saying the doctor. The minister. Or - or - a schoolteacher. Oh aye, teachers, aye. Chief toffs again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Can you think of any sort of people who belonged to anot
her class from yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 
Oh - aye, oh - the down and out, och aye, och aye, plenty of people, oh aye. You see -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 What kind of people were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 
You see - there was - there was what they - there was what they - they would be tradesmen. You 
see, they would be - engineers, joiners and that, all - you know, all the people as tradesmen. Well even those - people have grades if you like to grade them, you see, that they - a - an engineer - an engineer would - would be a higher grade than a plumbe
r
, as we'll say. You understand now what I'm getting at. Well - the likes of - my dad for instance you see, well - you - you would say he was a higher grade than the rest of them in the village, because he was the highest paid man in the village. But didna
 
make him any higher in grade. But he was highest paid man. So he was always - his children were all better fed, better - clothes than the others, but that was the only difference. That was the only difference. Because if you had a struggle - my mother was
 
away out giving some of the other kiddies - I think I told you already in a previous session, that - every morning there was two loafs cut up, take it into the children that was poorer in the school, did - didn't I tell you that? Perhaps told you that. Ay
e
, and the - in the morning - my mother had got - we're all getting ready for school, mother would cut up two loafs, in slices, and put either - margarine, butter or treacle, or a combination of the three of them probably, and you had to take that to schoo
l with you and give it to the - what they're calling the poorer children, that's what you were getting at - at isn't it, the cooper children. That's some that just werenae so well off as you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 What sort of families would they belong to, would they come 
from, these poorer children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 
Well they - no, they were just - their - they - I - I'm drawing the lines of demarcation and I don't believe in the demarcation now but - but you've got to do it sometime I know. Well - you see, a tradesman - there'd mayb
e be two or three different lines of demarcation in a tradesmen. And then there'd be - two of these lines between different trades. The point - the question you ask now. And then they're coming to the labourer. Now that's what you're after. The labourer, 
t
hey're - they're - they're on the bottom, they're on the bottom grade. Well it's a strange thing I'm going to say to you how, and it's funny, there's still grades in the labouring class too. That's funny. So the other was - the ones that - the lowest - in
 the labouring grade, that - that is the lowest. That's the down and outs, practically.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 
Can you remember being brought up to treat one sort of people different from another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 You mean - religiously?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Just in everyday life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Brought up different from another?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 To treat people differently?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 
No, we - we - we - we were all seemed to get on together, it didna matter what grade you were in. There - there were no - no side or no bias, no - no nothing at all. You were all Jock Thompsons 
bairns, will I put it that way. All Jock Thompsons bairns, that was those - didna matter what wages you had or - or where you were, it didnae matter.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Were you ever told to touch your cap?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 What?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Ever told to touch your cap?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Well - that
 was a bone of cnetntion was that because we boys you understand, of course you never - it never was in Glasgow, but in the wee village first of all - the village next to us, they all touched their caps to - the man of the manor, the mayor, you know. But 
our boys wouldnae do it. Oh no, we went out in strike. And - I'm talking about schoolboys now you know. No, no. We refused. To touch our caps. He's no better than us. No better than us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 That was the only person?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 That was the - aye, and the - and 
the minister of course. Oh yes. You had to touch your cap to the minister then, it didnae matter whether you belonged to - what grade you were in or anything. Even the - even the - the highest man in the village - had to touch his cap to the minister. Or 
the priest, mind you, oh no, no even a priest, aye, the priest as well, aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Was there anyone that you called sir or madam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 
Well - you see - this is a - this is a strange thing too. A lot of women resented - you called them madam. Oh yes. You see
, well - this is - this is just a - sort of - invention you could say an invention during the last - fifty years, this madam - back through the years you know this - thing but - well you see, it was bought over from France, that. And they didn't like that
 
at all. Them - them being - called something that was - that was French, see, oh no. Oh the women dinna like it, don't call me madam at all, I'm mistress so and so and Miss so and so. Just the same as my mother now, if anybody called me Jimmy - or or Jimm
o
ck or - she resented it, only because of it you see, she - she says she fell out with 'em. She says, my son's name is James. That's what's on his papers James, and James it's got to be in this house. Call him what you like outside but in the home here - J
ames. Oh she was very strict that way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Was there any man that you called sir?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 No. No even a foreman. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Can you remember anyone showing respect to your parents in this way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Oh yes. Oh a lot of - a lot of them showed respect for the d
ad. Oh aye. Oh he'd get called sir when he was going anywhere. Oh aye. But - it was just - it was just a name, you see what I mean, it was just - where are you going today sir? Are you going down to that meeting? Sir. You - you see - what I mean, it was j
u
st a - it - it - it didna really mean anything, it was just - you might as well have said - where are you going today Jimmy, or something like that, but that was too familiar you see so they couldna say that so they just said - sir. But however it meant n
othing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 In the village who were considered the most important people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 
The most important - the really most important man in the village was the minister. Or the priest.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 How much contact did you have with him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 I - I never had any contac
t if I saw him first. Neither did anybody else. They were off.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Why do you think he was considered important?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Oh because he was near to God.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 It was just fear was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Yes, that was it. That was the idea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Who did he associate with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 
Who did he associate with? Well - the only person I knew him associated with would - would - would be his wife, that's the only one, aye, that's the only - person I could - ever remember him associating with.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 What about the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Our teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Who did they associate with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 
Well, you see - the teachers long ago - may have been at school with your father, the same school. You understand, didnae go to colleges or nothing, they just grad - they just graded from the school and then
 - the one school to another. No, when I went to - I'll just - I'll just instance it to you now. I'd go to - went - as I told you, were down in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}England{\*\xmlclose}
{\*\xmlclose} for a wee while. Well - our land down in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}England{\*\xmlclose} and of course - the Scotch people had a great name - down in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}England{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
, for being educated. So they were at that time, much further ahead than English at that time. Well, when I - when I landed in it surprised me. The headmaster called me up. He started to examine me. Started to ask me questions. I was miles ahe
ad of him and he was a schoolmaster. Aye. A schoolmaster. So that shows you - the kind of - of ed - of education at that time. You - you - the - and if you wanted - now - I - I - I was teaching that - I was teaching that class when I was twelve - twelve a
nd a half year old. Twelve and a half year old teaching and - and I could - I could have - teached the headmaster too as I told you. So that - the - the - the education in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname 
country-region}}England{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} was very very very bad, very very low at that time, oh dear, aye. That's one thing we had in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}Scotland{\*\xmlclose}
{\*\xmlclose}, very strict a big cane in their hand you know, the three R's and you just - you had to know - you'd to do it. Here in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}England{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 they just seemed to -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Who would the teachers associate with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Beg pardon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 The teacher would presumably live in your village?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Oh yes. Oh - oh aye, they always lived locally.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Who were their friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 
Ah well, there you are, I don't know who their friends were, but the - the only - the only friends I could say a teacher would hav
e would be the schoolmaster, the doctor, or another teacher, that's the only friends they had because - you couldna associate with other people you see. No, they were a bit high, too high, for - for the rest of us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 What about shopkeepers, who did they associate with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 
Well - the shopkeeping in those days was nothing like the shopkeeping we have nowadays. It was a - a rough and ready sort of style. No, the - I knew one or two of them, in - in fact there's one or two of them I - I knew very well. Bu
t you said shopkeepers and that - that's what they were, shopkeepers. Just shopkeepers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 They were thought of as being much the same as yourselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 
Yes. They were ignored outside of that you see because - they were supposed to be a bit of your en
emy, a shopkeeper was a bit of your enemy, if he's a grocer - they were always cheating you, were always cheating you, you understand. So - really - he was at loggerheads with the rest of the - community, more or less, yes. You could say that he was sent 
to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4529087\charrsid8538783 Coventry}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783  most of the time. That - that was just about it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Did he have any friends at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Not that I know of. The only time he'd any friends is when they wanted tick.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 What about the local farmers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Well, the local farmers, they were
 very good, they were very good to everybody. Even in - even in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Glasgow{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 you know they were very good to you. And if you wanted, you'd got to - say - say - say - could I have a - turnip? Ah he wouldna mind. None wasted. If you see a \{BLANK\} that you want, j
ust - go - leave - leave as much - alone as you can, don't tread on anything that you can help, and go and lift that one that you wanted, and bring it out. Don't take the head off it there. Take that head off it when you go home. Don't leave all your rubb
ish lying about the field. See, you know, knocking the head off there. None of that, that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Who were their friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 
Who was the farmers friends? Oh he hadnae any friends either. No, no, oh no, oh no. He was at loggerheads with everybody. Everybody he knew - he was at loggerheads with everybody and everybody was at loggerheads with him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Even though he gave you the food?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 
Even though he gave us the food, aye. I tell you, you were only awful friendly when you wanted anything, or got anything you see, you were awful pals then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 What about employers? Did you come across any employers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 
Employers? Oh aye. Well there were plenty employers. Managers and under-managers, och aye. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Who did they associate with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 
Well - I could - they're not supposed to associate with any, but they associated with anybody at all. Go for a drink with the men or anything. Out of their own district. But not in their own district. Oh no. The likes of me now - you're a manageress and I
'm a - just a worker. But we're quite - pally in the work you know. You - you're the head one - and I'm a pretty good worker. See what I mean? So - if we're - well - outside if you wanted to have a social life you'd to go away to a different part of town,
 to have that social life, see. It was just was not the done thing, no.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 What sort of people would you say went to church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 
Went to church? Well the - that - the - from the middle class upwards goes to church mostly, that's it. But - but lower than that never bother about church at all. Never bother about church. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 What about the chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 
Well, the chapel, everyone goes to - I'll hand that to the - Roman Catholics. Is compelled to go, they have to go. Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Was that the way in your village?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 
Oh - oh my, very much so, not so much now they're - they've a lot of leeway - there's more laxity now in the - Roman Catholic church than they had in my day, oh my goodness, oh the old priest with the old - came in his \{BLANK\} They was terri
fied for the priest, the - the schoolboys especially, aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 
In the village where you lived did all the people in the working class have the same standard of living?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Mostly, yes. mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Were there any different groups?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Well - the only thin
g they - they - they'd a higher standard of living, I'll qualify that in a minute or two. Only time they'd a higher qualify - standard of living is when they come into Glasgow. You see. And it may be any - may be any days of the week or - or - or mostly w
eekend, they come in there, and they - they got a higher standard of living then because - they bought big - you know, they buy a ham, a whole ham you see or - was a whole cheese or - or - or a hag - or a cod you know, big cod and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 You'd do that yourself would you as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Yes. Yes. Oh they did it, oh aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 
Can you remember a family who belonged to a different group from you? Were you familiar with any family that you could describe to me?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 You could what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 That you could describe to
 me, who belonged to a different group from yourselves?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 
Well - the - the - the only - the only people I - I could describe to you would be some of my own aunts and uncles - that were great christians. Well - although they belonged we'll say to the w
orking class - group, that's the ones you want isn't it - but they - didn't associate with us at all, because - oh no. Oh no, because they were a higher grade of christians than us, you understand. They were - the - I don't know whether you - ever heard -
 well you do, you - you - you've read it in the paper every day say, these groups that are in the North of Scotland, yet there's some in the North of Scotland yet. I don't think there's any in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Glasgow{\*\xmlclose}
 at all, there may be some in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Glasgow{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}. It's the Brethren.
 The Plymouth Brethren was the first lot that came, the Plymouth Brethren, they lived very strict you see, very - very strict code, where you can scarcely believe that you're breathing the wrong - air, breathing the wrong air - the wrong air, see what I m
ean, very very strict. Well }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4529087\charrsid8538783 that\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 
 way you could classify - two people, the likes of - of - brother and sister, or two sisters, two brothers, and the in the one house \{BLANK\} If they're members of the Plymouth - Plymouth Brethren. Oh very strict. Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 
What about in your village, did you know any other families who had say a lower standard of living than yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 
Och aye, a whole lot of families, lower standard of living than ourselves. Oh aye. Oh aye. I mean the railways workers for instance like
 that. They - they - they were on lower standards of life, because a railway worker at that time - you'll no believe this, a railway worker at that time was anything - from - sixteen to eighteen shillings a week, that was his pay. A porter, you know, a po
rter. Sixteen to eighteen bob a week. Yes, for a twelve hour week - twelve hour day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 It must have been very difficult for them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 
Oh the living was terrible. It was bad, bad. You see sometimes - you see all these strikes that we're having just now?
 I think this is the aftermath of all that. That these men the likes of me that was older and suffered all that, you're pumping it into the youngsters. And they're pumping it into their youngsters and that's what's the cause of this now. What they suffere
d - in their young days. I think that's - a cause of a lot of these strikes and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Do you think that one group in your village felt itself superior to others?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 
No. No, no excepting - in the religious line, yes. But outside of the religious line
, no. The Roman Catholics - Presbyterians - all the religious groups - except the Plymouth Brethren, they - they were all - pally and chummy - out - outside of the church. Oh yes, they were.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Were some families thought of as rough and others as respectable?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Were what?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Were some families thought of as rough?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 
Oh - oh - well - you - you - you know what happens nowadays. It's just the same nowadays as happened in my day. As people get on a lot in the world and they watch what they've got -
 and other people who should be in the same standard as them but are not because they don't watch what they've got. Now that's maybe what you were after. They both got a different standard of life altogether. But they ought to both have the same, because 
t
hey're both of the same - money. But the one - the one, he spends and gambles his money, and - and smokes, the other one doesn't do anything. He just attends to the home. Well - the women mind you, I'm no - I'm no drawing the women the women are just as b
a
d as men. You'll now some of them, there's - pretty bad some of them too. They're going to bingo and all these things, they can spend a pound or two in no time. No, that's the only kind of - differentiation that I could put between - them that way. But - 
i
f - if you - if you meet a man - who - I'll - this - this is - this is one against myself. I come into a pub this day - and I - I got to the bar and I'm going away to order a drink, and I - I - there was a man that was along with me, another man at the ba
r
, he says, that's all right chum. Glass of whisky and a pint. Now that - that - that was - that was put down in front of me, well - that was like two of them that was together, and me, one of the two were joining me. Another fellow was along with him says
 
to him, I thought you told me you wasna pally with him, you wouldnae you wouldnae talk to him? Oh, he says, so I did, in the work. That's right. But outside's different. He says, we're pals, he said, he said, we're no pals in the work, he said, because he
'
s my guv'nor. He give me my orders. You see what I mean - that - that was like - there were no enmity between us or anything. Barring - he - he said in the work - there's that old bugger coming again - we'd better watch it, we're getting it, there's nothi
ng to it though, anybody hearing it - would - would say oh he's got a right - a right deal with that fellow, there - there's no palling they two. \{BLANK\}
 Well that gives you an idea of how - how a lot of them are. There's pals - outside the work but inside the work was just - no, not }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4529087\charrsid8538783 pally}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 
Do you remember a distinction being made between craftsmen and labourers in your village?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 
Oh aye, I've seen that - I've seen that in the work too, in the works here in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Glasgow{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, big - big public works, yes. Defi
nitely. I've seen a tradesman who wouldn't go into - we'll say a - a - when it came to the meal hour they'd a bothey to go to, what they called a bothey, just a bothey you know, just an eating room. They're going there and a - a tradesman wouldnae go in t
here. No. No with a labourer, they considered them labourers. Wouldnae go in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Has that always been the case in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Glasgow{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 
It's always the same, that's always been the case since ever I remember. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 What about their families, was there the s
ame sort of distinction outside the work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 
Oh well, the only part of the family ever showed a distinction outside the works the women. Oh and they do show it. Oh yes. If - if - I'm the foreman - you're you're just the 1 worker, no - no - I'll no say -
 I hate the word labourer, I hate to use the word, they were just the workers, you see. And - and the wife of - of one - his wife of worker. See? You darenae put on the same hat as me. You understand. Probably you can afford it. Supposing I went in and go
t a nice hat like that, say that - thing there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 
Did your mother and father treat people in different classes the same as they treated everybody?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 
Oh yes, they was all treated alike, even - even the minister's wife and the - ordinary labourer's wife, they were all treated alike just the same. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Do you think that your mother saw herself as belonging to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4529087\charrsid8538783 a particular}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783  social class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 
My mother actually - visualized herself in a better class than the class she was in Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Why do you think so?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 
Well - in her talk, and - how she was trying to - educate us herself, apart from what you were getting at school. And she was very - she was very - she looked like an - an aristocrat, really I - I shouldn't be saying this but really - she lo
oked and talked - like an aristocrat. Gently, but very convincingly, you know. That was her - she was a very gentle woman as I - I think I told you that already. I never saw her striking anyone actually. But she was a - I think that answers that question.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 
Do you think when she thought of herself in this way, belonging to a higher social class, do you think this was because of her parents perhaps?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 
No, no, it - she was a refined - she was - a very refined looking woman, an aristo - more refined than the ordinary - country woman that you would see. To look at her you would have thought she was a different class altogether. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 She was from the country wasn't she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 She was from the country. She was a country child.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Do you think there was any reason other than her looks why she thought this?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 
No. No. No. There was no reason for that at all I wouldn't think. But you there's some of us have dreams, I don't know whether you've got it or not, where you think that you belong to a bett
er class than the class you're in. Perhaps you've never come across it, but you - you will come across with certain dreams when you're dreaming, or even when you're waking tool. But - that - that's her feeling I think of people, whether it's a - whether -
 
whether it's a throw back, to something you see, we're all supposed to be throw backs to another generation altogether, we miss one or two generations, it says - it says that in the Bible you see. So I - I think perhaps that perhaps you miss a generation 
o
r two before - the same thing arises. She may have thought that - that she - she - she'd arrived in the wrong place coming, she'd come from a better generation, she'd arrived in another. I - I don't know that mark you, I'm just visualizing that that - tha
t was her thoughts.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 At that time was it possible to move from one class to another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 
To - oh yes, oh there - oh there were no distinctions made as far as that, if you'd money. If you'd money. Oh yes. Oh there were no distinctions made as far as class was concerned at that time. Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 You could become of a higher class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 
Yes. If you had the money, you could become - one of the toffs. You - I don't think you have beat the minister, or the doctor. In estimation of the rest of the people. But you could have - you - could have come into a higher class.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Can you remember anyone who did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 
Well - I could re - remember few trades unions men advancing, but that was - that's a different thing altogether. Advancing into a higher class. I can remember quite a few of those. 'Cos they were in our house pretty often. Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 That was because they began to earn more money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 
Yes, because they were earning more money and - and they were - they were - were the - you seemed to get something wh
en you're in control of men and you get more control of men. You - you - you seem to get something - that tells you that - that you're better than them, you might not be any better but - but it seems to - put something into you that makes you think - that
 you're above that class. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Can you remember anybody being described as a real gentleman or a real lady?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 
Well - I've heard plenty of people described that way. Without any - anything - you - you see - in - in the country, oh you see it here too
 - you would - see someone perhaps walking up the street. You get some of them in here. And - you would say to yourself, oh - that lady's out of - she's out of class here. She looks like a lady, not like a worker at all. But - but as far as - that's only 
- distinction I can draw.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 
Is there anybody in particular who was described like that, from your childhood?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 
Well - I - I could tell you that we - the - we had one - we had one - minister's wife - this is - this is it - had one minister's wife, an
d she was out of class altogether. Oh yes. She was of - the lower working side I would say. You understand? But she was still the minister's wife and had to be treated as a minister's wife. But very - sparingly treated her - if you - if you get what I mea
n. Just because the - they had to do it - to present - lady so and so or - something - it was very }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4529087\charrsid8538783 grudging}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783  but they just knew that she was a minister's wife and she - they had to - treat her as a minister's wife. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Do you remember seeing a policeman around when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 
Oh you very very - not often when you saw a policeman but - well - well I'm maybe a little wrong there when I say that. There was always a policeman parading round about. Different from now altogether. You - the - the p
olicemen were friends of yours then. Now the - police are enemies, at least we make them our enemy now. But at that time a policeman was your friend. Although, if you saw one - you - you ran away from him. Just the same you were afraid of them. But you di
dn't have to be afraid of them because - they - they - they was really - if I could coin a phrase they were really gentlemen. I'm coining a phrase now. But they were really gentlemen, policemen at that time, yes, mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 What about when you moved to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Glasgow{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, was there any difference in the policemen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Well - the - the difference in of course - in 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Glasgow{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 you - you - you had to be smarter, you had to be quicker in your thought. Because the country was a slow type you see, tomorrow if - if - tomorrow'll do tomorrow'll do. You see, they - they - they wasnae in a hurry to do anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Were the policemen more }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4529087\charrsid8538783 sophisticated}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783  in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}
Glasgow{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Oh much more. Oh yes. Oh much more.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Were they friendly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Well, yes, yes, I would say, yes, they were jus
t as friendly. Within - within sort of - limits we'll say, you see - a policeman in the country - could be a friend. Because it was a recognized thing. But when you come to a town, in a town like {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Glasgow{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} - if you - if you was friendly with someone, or if y
ou appeared to be friendly with someone, you see that was the talk then. Oh, so and so's all right with the police, he can do what he likes. You understand what I mean now? Well that - that - that's the difference, aye. Could - could draw - the difference
s at that time.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 How do you think the policeman treated the people in general?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 
Well - up until the general strike - they treated them - like their fathers and mothers you know what I mean, sons and daughters and - everything. But after that mind 
you it was quite different. Oh yes, because there was a lot of brutality used during the general strike. Oh yes. Quite a lot of brutality. Not saying the policemen were all to blame themselves because - the - the men - they never - the women never engaged
 
in anything like that at that time. The men - the men you see would become slightly brutalized through want. Not so much for themselves, but more for their family - having to do without. They were slightly brutalized with that, and hence they were doing t
hings which in the normal course they would never have done. So that made the policemen do things that they wouldn't have done either. But they - they had to reply with - force with force.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 But before that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Oh - oh before that \{BLANK\} whatever you like to make it, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 In Glengarnock was your home rented?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Oh yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Did you see anything of your landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Beg pardon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Did you see anything of your landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 No. He - he - oh there - there werenae - they - they just
 came now and again like. Aye, they just came when - there's no offices or anything in it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Who was your landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Ay?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Who was your landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 
Now I couldn't tell you who was the landlord, but I could not tell you who was the landlord. 
'Cos there was quite a lot of houses of course, although I'm saying it was a country village there were a lot of houses in it you know. Got three or four hundred houses in it - spread away out you know, all over the place, but everyone knew everyone.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 What about when you came to Glasgow, was your house rented then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 
Oh yes, oh they - it was tenements then. We - we were all in tenements, there were very few of these kind of houses then. It was only up this end of the town you got all this style of house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Did you see your landlord then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 
Oh aye, och aye. Well - I don't suppose it was the landlord, it would be his agent. Yes, the - yes - be his agent. It wouldn't be the landlord.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Did you have any feelings about your landlord at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 
Och well - I wouldn't like to tell you that. Had some pretty hard feelings about him. Oh and they are that yet of course, but he's not to blame for anything. He just collects - what they're supposed to collect. But we -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Did you find the rents high?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 
But you never really saw - the man that owned the flats see, if that's what you mean you never - you don't see them yet. You never see the man that }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4529087\charrsid8538783 owns}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783  the property yet. He's an agent that - that - that agent - engages someone else, the man that co
llects money, and goes round and does and all the dirty work. That's still the - still the same today as it was then, only on a bigger scale now of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Do you remember feeling that your parents had a struggle to make ends meet?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Well - when -
 when I left - as I told you, I was told to leave - they asked me to leave the school. I was crying. That's when I knew they was having a struggle to make ends meet. Oh yes. That would be when I was fourteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 You were in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Glasgow{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 That was in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Glasgow{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Do you think they had more of a struggle when they came to 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Glasgow{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 
Oh - dear, aye, there's no struggle in the country. Oh no, no. You were poor, they were all poor, but you could go always go as I told you, go and get a turnip o
r some potatoes, as long as you let - didn't destroy anything. If you needed a turnip you went and got one, but you didn't - didn't destroy half a dozen getting one, you just - took one.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 When you got to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Glasgow{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} it was different, it was harder was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 
Well, when you - when you got to Glasgow, you - if you wanted anything like like you'd a little further to travel. Which made a difference.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 
What did you think about it when you found out that your parents were having a struggle?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Well - we
 just had to go and try and get money somewhere. You went with papers or - any - give a coalman a wee hand to - or somebody a hand, or a - a - anything - to any shopkeepers was - maybe needing a sweeper up or something. Anything to get a copper or two, go
ing with milk, going with papers. Anything to get a copper or two.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 
What difference did it make to your family if your father was ill or out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 
Well at that time it didn't make any difference at all. No. You see, that - as I told you, the - the last man they paid - is the doctor. So \{BLANK\}
 the doctor, whatever medicine he was - getting, but if they could pay they would pay and if they couldnae pay they got it. Well it was just the same, you know, it was a communal thing. If you couldn't pay you got just the same. Went down in }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4529087\charrsid8538783 the}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 
 book and it might not. And the - the likes of me when the - when the - when the wife's mother died - she - she'd been owing for a lot of years, but she never let on. Very - independent she was. She never let on that 
she'd one or two wee bills that she had never paid up. So we got these bills in, after she was dead. Well - they were paid just the same. We - we paid them, you know, we - we just paid them. There was nothing very big. A few shillings. But that was all sq
uared up - without - hushed up you know, nobody - nobody knew anything about them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 
What about when your father was out of work, what difference did that make to your family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 I don't think my father was ever out of work. He - he just went away to 
another place and got another job you see. Oh aye. Oh there were none of this going - there were no - not any dole or anything at this time, you - we - we're - we're well back just now, away back.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Did you ever get any help from the Guardians or the Parish?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 
No. No, no, I remember - I remember once - someone - now wait 'til I see now, aye, it was - my father was - away looking for work. And - I - I told you about the Plymouth Brethren didn't I? Told you about them. Well - you see, my - my mother wa
s a member of that - sect. And they told her how she could get money - with - to keep a loan. But you see - whenever we mentioned it was from the Parish you see, them was from the Parish then you understand, it was from the Parish, oh - oh no. No, no. Don
't want anything off the parish. Just did without. Aye.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Why do you think she didn't want anything from the Parish?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 
Well that - that was the - this was this - idea, the old Scottish people have it yet, that - that they'll no - they'll no take anything that they don't earn. Pou}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4529087\charrsid8538783 
r}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783  understand, this is an old Scots independence, it's a lot of blooming tripe you know but - but - but that was the idea. Yes, that's how they felt.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Did you know anybody who had help from the parish?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 How did the parish treat them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 
Oh just like brutes. This is - this is also away back, you know. Oh aye, just like brutes. They're just kicked around like animals. In the parish. I'm sorry to say that, but that - that's true.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 If there was someone 
in your village that they people disapproved was there any special way in which they showed it? Do you remember for example anybody being made to leave by rough music?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 
No, no, no, but - the only people that I knew - disapproving were the people at - that went - off their head. There are plenty of them nowadays, but - there was plenty then I suppose then, but - only an odd one that you knew about.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Was there any way in which everybody showed their disapproval?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Well - in - in a case like that,
 we just think - you'd have said they disapproved it, they did the very opposite. They were very kind to these people. Aye, over kind to them. Yes. That's right. These people got far better off. You - you'd have heard them saying \{BLANK\}
 But - this is all play and no work. It used to be all work and no play then, all play and no work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Did you ever come across rough music?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Beg pardon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Did you ever come across rough music?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Rough music?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Do you know what that is?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 When people make a noise outside somebody's house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Well the - the nearest we came to that was what we call the German Bands.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 What was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 
They - they travelled up and down the country with a big - drum. We - we called them German Bands bu
t - later on they called them German spies, there's maybe three or four in a company you see, they - they made a devil of a noise. It - it - it was for money, they were getting money you know. And - and some of the other - some of them - would - would hav
e a - a bear, a big bear, went round and - did a lot of tricks you know. For money too. Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Would they go to the village green? Or round the houses?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Oh round - no, they - they just went in the main street \{BLANK\}
 in the main street, and travelled, all around the streets. I'm saying the main street, there were nae main streets then. There's just wee roads. But - that's - that - well - these men that had the bears - when I look aback on it \{BLANK\}
 the things were wild you know. Well they looked wild anyway, they'd a muz - they'd a muzzle on them right enough but they didna need to hit you with a muzzle, only hit you with one of the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4529087\charrsid8538783 paw}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 
 was enough to kill you. That's how they travelled up and down from village to village, right up through - {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}Scotland{\*\xmlclose}, I suppose they travelled through {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}England{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} too. We only met them in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}Scotland{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Can you ever remember an effigy being made?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 
An effigy? Oh aye, oh aye, I remember effigies being made. When - when - when they didna like a Prime Minister or someon
e like that. Oh heavens, you know, the - the German Kaiser and - and - De - Dewitt, that was the - that was the Boer - the Boer man. They - that - the - they'd effigies for those, that - is that what you meant. This - these people, aye, that's right, oh a
ye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 In the village and in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Glasgow{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 In the village and in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Glasgow
{\*\xmlclose}, I've seen them in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Glasgow{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 What did they do with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 They burn them. Burn them, oh aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Was there anything else like that? I suppose it was black magic really?

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 
Well it wasna black magic, but there was a lot of things that was blamed on black magic, you know, there was a lot of things blamed on that. Oh aye, yes. Old superstitious business, aye. There used to be a certain - a certain place that you wouldn
a go over that place at night, after a certain time of night. And there was some bridges and if you went over them you said a wee prayer on the road over. A lot of things like that. Oh aye, oh - old superstitions. I can always keep in mind the dad telling
 
us he was - he was travelling - they'd to do a lot of travelling you know in looking for their work, they didn't just go down to the corner and look for work, and he was travelling from - from - Kilmarnock to Glengarrock, quite a wee - it's about fifteen 
o
dd mile. And he's coming along this country road. And of course you know the hedges along the country road. And all the time he was coming up for - for about - he said for about a couple of mile - about when he - when he - when he was walking this walk, a
n
d whenever he stopped it stopped. So he got that mad and he said to the hedge he said, come to hell out of there you bugger where I can see you, we'll have a right fight if that's what you want. Know what it was? A cow. A cow. Cow was paddling - padding a
long. When he - when he got up to the side, going - moooo. Said he got the shock of his life \{BLANK\}
 It was a cow. Put its head over the side and said, moooo. So that was the kind of thing you had - I suppose you would call that - he - the thought that was magic that was following him. Until it puts its head over. Cone to the end of the road.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Were you ever given lessons by one of your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Very }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4529087\charrsid8538783 selfdom}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 . Didn't bother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Did you ever have a tutor or a governess?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 How old were you when you first sent to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 
Well I would say - when I first went to school, I don't - don't think we got going before that time, I think you - a boy had to be - had to be - four, and a girl had to be five. Before they got into school. There
 were none of this - small school you could - sit and play around - this is at the very beginning I'm talking about. Latterly, you - you could - get into school and just sit around, playing at anything. Nobody teaching you or anything, you were just in th
e playground and the - the - you got - the - the band hall. And that - that's where you all played, it was the kiddies, all the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4529087\charrsid8538783 kiddies}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 , they put them all in there you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 When you first started school what time of the morning did you go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Nine o'clock.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 When did you come back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Well - what for - for keeps? Twelve o'clock. Twelve o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 You just went to the morning school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Oh no. No, no. You - that - that was that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Then you came back at twelve and what time did you go back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Well you'd to be back in the - in the school half past - half past one.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 What time did you come back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 
Four o'clock. The children of course came at three. The young - the young children. They come - they came out at three o'clock. The older ones is four.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Did you ever go to just an afternoon school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Beg pardon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Did you ever go to school just in the afternoons?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 No. No, we never had to do that, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 What kind of school was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Oh just a small - country s
chool. In fact - there werenae much better in Glasgow when we come into Glasgow at first, the schools werenae - very much better.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Was it a church school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 No. No, no. A Corp - oh no, it's a - a county school. County school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Was it boys or girls or mixed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Mixed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 How did you get to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 You walked.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 How long did that take you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 
Oh we some - sometimes got it - there was one time I was about three mile. Three miles, but other times I said probably oh - couple of hundr
ed yards. Was one time as I say when we come through the park - through the fields, well say through the fields, say a bit proper - through the fields, say a bit proper - through the fields, well that - that would be quite a time. About three mile and jus
t young at the time.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Who would go with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Oh there'd be plenty.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 All the village children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 
There was a whole lot, no, they wouldna be all there, oh no. But all those over in that - row of houses - would - would go there, not all the 
village children, just some of them. See there might have been some - some at this village, some at that village, some at that village, all going to the same school and all converging from different - roads, you see what I mean.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Was the school very far away, the school was quite near was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 
The school was quite near. In the village. It was just in the centre of the village. The central spot in the village was the school. And all - in all the villages I knew.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Sometimes though you'd just take a detour would you, round the fields?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Aye. That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Did you always have your midday meal at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 
You always had your - dinner at night at home, when dad come home from his work. That's when you got dinner. At night. You never got a 
- a - a - a - what you would call a hot meal through the day. It was just the - you may have got a plate of porridge or something if you were lucky. But - but mostly you'd maybe get a plate of soup or something. But you would get no meat or anything until
 dad come home at night. That was the one - that was our - meal of the day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 What did you think of school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 
I told you. I thought - I thought it was great. But that's no what they all - all - they all thought, oh no. I - didn't - I didn't think it 
was great in the beginning but - when it come near the time for - to leave school, that's when I - maybe a couple of years before that, that's when I was taking an interest in things at the school. And I really didn't - oh I could say that on the Bible, I
 really didn't want to leave the school at all. Didn't want to leave at all.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 How did you feel about the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 
Well there's some of them - some of them - they used to tell me I was a teacher's favourite. Aye, I used to get the blame of that. 
But - the - the - the trouble with that was I think is because - the - I was always right. Oh that's not any bragging, that's - that was the truth. That was the truth. That - well I studied a lot more than the rest. But when they weren't in school, - that
 was it finished. But when I went home I - did a few lessons, the same as they do nowadays.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 
Did the teachers emphasise certain things as important, such as manners and tidiness?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Well - to be quite frank with you - I think the teachers had to be t
aught themselves a lot of times from the children. Aye. Now that's putting it bluntly. Yes, I think some of the - teachers werenae so good themselves. It was just the - the - the youngsters, like me we'll say, doing - going up 'til about eight to twelve, 
you'd been taught all your manners at home. You - you saw that had to be carried out at - at school, that's what I'm saying, some of these teachers were taught off us - off the children instead of the - them teaching the children. Yes, that's quite true.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 
When you moved to Glasgow, first of all you moved down to Warrington didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Did you go to school in Warrington?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Was there a lot of difference, you were saying that they weren't so good?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Oh - oh I told you weren
't nearly - oh no, they werena near so good in Warrington, oh no, no, no. Miles behind us. Miles behind us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 What about the teachers, how did you feel about the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 The teachers didna know anything about it. You see, what - what the schools
 were running then - maybe - maybe you know something about them, maybe not, they were only - pupil teachers as we called them, PT's. Well they - they were just - youngsters like you or me or anyone at school. You were studying for - then they called you 
p
upil teachers, but you're still in charge of a class. You understand? So that that was how you were taught then. There were - I don't think - I think at the school - at Kirklee Bank school I - I don't think the headmaster even was a qualified man. I'm qui
te sure he just come out the army. I'm just - my mind just doesnae run so good as that, but I'm quite sure that that man just come out the army. Right into being a - a schoolmaster in that - a small school, just a small school you know. That's it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 What about when you came to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Glasgow{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, what difference was there you found there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 
Oh well, you - you'd a lot of qualified teachers when we came to Glasgow, but you still had a lot of PT's in Glasgow too. Oh yes. But they - they only - they only teached - 
up - about - the first standard, second standard you see, or else given - a - a - a - an older class, teaching an older class and they get a PT along with them. You see, just to go in and check - stuff, see what we're doing of, work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Did you used to start and finish school at the same times in 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Glasgow{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 
Oh yes, oh they - that - that's a standard for the whole country. That - that stood for the whole country. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 When you got to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Glasgow{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, the teachers in the school there, did they emphasise more things like manners and tidiness, punctuality?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Oh -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Were they any different?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 
Well - in a refined way, yes. But as far as - as manners and everything was concerned - I think they were - kids from the country was teaching the - the ones from {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Glasgow
{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}. But in a refined way the - the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Glasgow{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} ones had it, you understand.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 What about ways of speaking, were any of the teachers hot on that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 On what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Ways of speaking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Why you're speaking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Ways of speaking, if you spoke nicely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 
No, no. No. The - they didnae - make you - speak - hoh hoh way you know. Was none of this - what was it you get - what was it you get at school now - oh what is it you get taught now - what is it the kiddies get taught now, they get taught it yet.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 English? Speech training?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Voice training, aye. What is it - brown cow is it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 How now brown cow?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 
How - aye, yes, brown cow you see. You didn't get any of that - 'til - 'til we come into Glasgow.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 You did then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 You - you did - you did then, did - you got that in 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Glasgow{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}. We - we thought it was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4529087\charrsid8538783 awfully}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783  silly, talking about how now brown cow. Isn't it. Didn't know it was voice training.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 What about punctuality?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Oh they was always very strict on that. Oh.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Boty in Glengarnock and Glasgow?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 
Oh aye. Very very - they might let you off with a little in Glengarrock, didn't let you off at all in Glas - no, no, you'd to - oh - stand up there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 How did you used to get to school in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Glasgow{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Ah well - the
re was buses that they called it at that - and then it - and then - a while after it was tram cars. But at the beginning there were just buses pulled pulled with horses you see. There was a - they were just like - like - like buses, buses we called them. 
And - and up and downstairs in them. And - and four or six handed - horses, you know, two, two and two, or just two and two. See? Trot along too. You thought it was great fun, we were sitting away up high, the - old horses trot - trotting along.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Had you far to go to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 
Well sometimes. Sometimes - as you advance in your schooling you see - you'd perhaps to go to a different village - to school you see. The like - the likes of - the likes of in Glengarnock there, we had to go to Beath. Or - or 
- for a higher grade of schooling. And then after the higher grade of schooling we'd to go to Troon. You see, well - you - you'd to - you'd to go in a train then. Go in the train to Troon. Because it was quite a wee distance.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Did you go to Beath?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Oh yes. Oh I was a - a scholar in - days, in - Troon, yes. Right.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 If you did something the teachers disapproved of what would happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Five of the best. Five of the best.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Girls the same as boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Girls the same as boys. Only - the boys got a bit harder, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 What offences would you have to commit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 
Oh - well - we - we - when you got the strap - when you got the strap - it had to be some - thing - some really thing. The other little things like mistakes in grammar or any
thing like that, there was just a little rap over the knuckles you know. You know, with a cane. Always a wee cane, but - you never see that. The teachers always had a cane going round the class you know, and just - give you a wee rap over the knuckles wit
h it, but that - that was all that was in it. When they lifted the strap to you believe me you'd done something. Aye. And you knew about it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Giving cheek, would that count?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Oh cheeking, oh aye, oh aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 That was serious?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Oh that was ser
ious. Oh aye. Well - anything in that line - or any telling lies or anything, that was - that was it, no, no, we - these - these were crimes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Did your parents show an interest in your school work?
