Prop - proper grammar. Proper grammar. Proper grammar, that's - that was the great thing. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 What about punctuality?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Oh you'd to be early. A
nd that went all the way. All the - that was - that was always. Being punctual, that was one - that was one of the
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 How would you be punished at Beath school, that was the second school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Oh well - I tell you - how - how you were punished at - at 
Ardeath school - You - you were - you've heard about the fool - a fool's cap? Fool's cap, foolscap paper you can have a foolscap paper, well you got a fool's cap. That's how you were punished at Beath school. You - you weren't - you weren't - didn't get s
trapped or anything, you'd to stand out in front of the class with a fool's cap on and - and what a silly - thing you - oh, and that's what you hate, that's why you wouldna get that, you see what I mean. Aye. Oh aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 That was for girls and boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 
No. Another - another way you got punished, we were late - we liked this punishment, they had to abandon it. If you - were talking - were talking in school you see - you - I was maybe talking to you, you see, and I would get caught Sy, James Luke - number
 one row. This was the girls, you'd to get - get among the girls, that was your punishment, oh you liked that. That didn't last too long that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 What about at Troon, how were you punished there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Well - at - at Troon, you were - you were punished mo
re by being kept in. Kept in at night, maybe for half an hour. Or maybe an hour. Or - or no play. You see, well you - you'd a quarter of an hour for play well you - perhaps you got that docked off you, and no - no play. You got playing right enough but - 
you werenae officially playing, you weren't playing with the boys or the girls, whatever it was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 What offences would you have to commit before you got a detention?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 
Oh well, there was so many things you could do you know, so many things we could d
o anyhow. Well, the thing is that - you would call them stealing but we didn't look at them as stealing. No, we didna look at it well - the likes of - as I was telling you already - gurd - gurdling a few fish, we didna think that was stealing. But it was 
s
tealing, you know, it was theft. And - any - apples falling off a tree, picking them off the ground, and eating them. That was stealing. We didn't think it was stealing. Because it had fallen. Or pears or anything at all. We just - anything that fell down
 
- we - that was the - that was the law. As long as it had fallen - you could eat it. And if you got caught I mean to say you got away with it if you - if you were caught because - they would just told you - and - that - that you'd plucked it. They - they 
wouldn't believe you that you'd picked it off the ground.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 At Beath did the other children come from similar types of homes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 
Oh yes. Ah you see - Beath - Beath at that time - was a sort of - an aristocratic village. What they made mostly was furn
iture. You see, and they're all tradesmen and the women - the women worked too, the women - women worked in the - making the furniture too. So that was a kind of - half aristocratic - for the time - for the times, for the times you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 So you'd get some of those children would you in the school?
