en me anything to stay. But they didna give me it when I was - thought I'd got another job. You understand what I mean? They - they're giving me ten - two pound a week at that time. I would have stayed there. Certainly I wouldn't have moved. That was an a
wful }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4529087\charrsid8538783 big wage}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 
 at that time, my goodness, that was - millionaire class, two pound a week. But you see, they didna offer it, but they'd offer me anything at all after I said I was leaving. Of course that happens all the time.
