Och, we - we went various places - it all depended on - on what - what age you start at you see. If we start at we'll say at fourteen, we just fid
dled around with the - the - the gang you see, you would say the gang, it was just a - just boys of our own chums you know, we called them a gang but - no gang attached to it. Well, we played with that, you play away - maybe a bit of cricket or something,
 rounders and football, and you'd maybe go for a ramble and do a bit of fishing. You see? And you might go for a ramble and do a bit of poaching. I shouldnae have told you that. That was - that was that. Mm.
