ell - well - they - they helped you by giving you - good presents and - and - and fixing your home up for you when you went into it, see, they - because at that time - in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Glasgow{\*\xmlclose}
 they were building - they were building {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Glasgow{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} at that time. You see. And al
l the buildings were these four storey - stated buildings then. So - there was no - no one required to give you a hand - to get a house, you could just go to a factor and he'd give you a dozen keys to go and have a look at them all. Aye. And you - you did
n't take one mark you - you didn't take one, unless they papered it and painted it for you. Oh aye, they had to paper and paint it or you wouldn't have it. Aye. That's true. Aye. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Were these homes to rent or to buy?
