 a lot of houses was like that. But no in our house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 
When your children were young did you feel that there was a right way or a wrong way of bringing them up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 
Well - you - I thought there was a right way of bringing them up - tried to abide by it but it may have been wrong you know. As far as - my - opinion was - that was how they were brought up, in that way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 
Did you and your wife have the same ideas about bringing up children or different ideas?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Well when they were younger - we'd a - 
it was a - a - an understood thing, there was nothing laid down. But we - wife had to do with the children - 'til they were ready for school. After that I took control. You - get what I mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Did you and your wife talk about this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Oh yes. Oh - o
h aye, oh maybe - blathers now and again you know. No - nothing in an argumentative way, just - just talking for - say, the - children are doing - doing well today, they're - doing everything in a proper manner you know. That after they're away. There was
 one time mind you I was fogged. I was really - I was really scared this day. We went to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Edinburgh{\*\xmlclose}, was a - it was a flower show in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname 
City}}Edinburgh{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, the King and Queen were there. I said to the wife, what do you say we go down there Margaret? She said, what's the sense of going with two children to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Edinburgh{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}? }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3224870\charrsid8538783 
Said, well we'll see something they've never seen in their life before, maybe never see it again, the two - the King and the Queen both, we'll see down Princes Street, and then we'll go and have - she said, t
hat's what I'm frighted of going - us going in there. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 
You're going into a hotel? I said, oh yes. She said you'll no go into a tearoom for a change? Says I, no. Went to a hotel. I says, this is where they're going to get taught. You know, they were - they w
erena - werena - the one would be about four and the other one would be about seven. I said, this is where they're going to get taught. We tried to teach them in here, well they're - they're going to face the music now, they're going with the toffs now. W
ent in - and her and I - I could - I was watching her and I'll bet you she was watching me. I was scared. But - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3224870\charrsid8538783 whether}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783  - whether we'd do anything or whether - you know - about a dozen spoons, knives and forks, and spoons all in front of you, I mean - to la
y a table. I was scared. God they never made a mistake. I don't now how they done it. Never made a mistake. Aye. Never made a mistake. As I - as I come the wife said, what do you think of that one? She says, my heart was in my mouth all the time but she s
a
id it was great, she says - she says, I - I was just greeting with pure happiness. Greeting when you're happy. But it was wonderful to watch them, it was the first time they'd ever been in public. Just started off - but that's all - that - well that - tha
t's coming yet, if they're - if children are properly taught when they're young - that bides with them. They never lose that. I don't think they do anyway.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Which King and Queen was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 I would say - King George IV or V or - King George the V was
 it, King George VI. Aye. That was - it was a flower show that was in Edinburgh, and they I they were attending it, they - they also went to Hamilton races right on the same day, they went to Hamilton races first and then they went to the flower show.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 
If you were worried about the children was there anyone that you used to talk to about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 
Well - we never talked to anyone except each other I don't think. Unless - unless before we came to Glasgow - they - you can always go round and talk to your 
doctor. Without the doctor seeing him at all. And then, the - the - the doctor would be passing you see, this was all done in ignorance today, if a child's ill the child wouldna know that - it's a doctor examining him. And he would come in to see - us, yo
u
 know what I mean, shake hands with you - have - have a good sit there then, kids went around - the kid was - he'd go away and he would tell you what - what it was he thought was wrong with this - bring in the medicine. And the medicine was in such a form
 that the child - still didnae know - the doctor had given him this medicines. You understand? It was all cheating.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 This was in Park Head was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 No, this was - this is in Park Head, aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Was your mother alive when your children were small?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 
My mother, yes. Oh yes. Mother was alive. Long while. She was alive - och aye. She was alive to the - she - what was she now - aye, that's right, she was - she was alive up to young Billy died, the one that was a minister. Yes. A minister.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 How often did you see her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 
My mother? Oh I saw her every day. No every day, every week. Every week. Father was dead of course long ago, he was dead.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Did you ask her advice in bringing up the children at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Now - that's a thing that I never d
id, I didn't like to mix two women. I left that to them and they could fight that out themselves.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Did she and your wife have the same ideas do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 
Well they seemed to be very - they seemed to know what each other wanted because I never heard - never heard my wife saying that - that my mother was - inquisitive or was - interfering with things or anything. They seemed to get - on fine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 What about your mother-in-law, was she alive when your children were small?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Oh yes, yes, yes, th
at's right. She was alive. Aye, that's right. She was - she was alive, aye, when the children were small, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 How often did you see her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 
Oh she was up there every day. My mother-in-law, oh aye, she was up - she was up every other day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Did you ever ask her advice about bringing up the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 No, she was a midwife you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Can you tell me some of the things that you }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3224870\charrsid8538783 felt}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 
 you ought to do for your children? Such as - were you very affectionate towards them when they were little?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 
Well, now - this is a very very - tricky question this, because - in my age - I'm talking about the whole age at this time, I'm not talking about me especially. They thought it was very }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3224870\charrsid8538783 effeminate}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783  to be too - affectionate to your children. Y
es. To a boy you couldn't be affectionate to him, or else you were bringing him up as a Jessie. Yes. Now that's the answer to your question, that's a straight answer. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 This was when you were a young man?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Yes, that's when I was a young man, and they - they were young men.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 
What about safety, were you very concerned that you should prevent their having accidents in the house and on the road?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 
Ah well, we didnae have - the traffic wasnae anything like it is today, and after all you - di
dnae - in fact, it - it was a good - it was a good laugh in our house for years, this - this is like with the oldest one - and his granny. Now - from - from our house - to where their granny stayed would be about a mile and a quarter. But he had to cross 
a
 street twice. You see. And he - he - his granny would be hanging out of that window, watching him crossing the street, and there were nothing on the street. This is the laugh. And she would be shouting after him, now John, watch yourself now, if there's 
something coming in a moment or two, just wait. There was nothing there for hours - going along these streets. If they did come it was a horse and cart or something you know. Going about two mile an hour. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Do you think your wife used to worry like that too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 
Aye, she worried too if he - if he was away out, in case he'd get run over with some of these wild horses that was about.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 What about food, did you feel you ought to give your children a proper diet?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Proper diet? No. No. We never studied diet at all at that time, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 What about discipline?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 
Oh discipline, oh they'd to be very - they'd to be very canny in their discipline, like, oh aye. And - and yet as I said, you - you never struck them. But you punished them. There's a lot of way of punishing you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Did you want your children to share their worries with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 
Oh well - I - I - I used to tell them that - they had anything - troubled them just come and tell me and - and that'd be all about it you see, well - i
f - if they come with it twice - and tell you and nothing happens, see they have confidence in you then, that you're not going to hit them. And that's what I found out anyway when I was quite young.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 How did you want your children to behave towards you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 
Oh well - I didnae want them to come in and say hellow Jimmy, how are you getting on? I -anted them to come in and say, well dad, how's things to night? You see. Or how's things this morning. That's how I wanted them to behave. There's some - some
 of the children nowadays you hear them come in and - I got wild with one grandchildren - grandchild now, and they're brought up very up to - posh level you know, and when his dad comes in he says - hello Jim, how are you getting on, this morning, or toni
ght? How are - how did you get on at work today, Jim? Of course he'll get away out of that you see. He's just young, just young. He - he'll leave away from that. So I don't bother really. See, he's just heard his - his mother saying Jim.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 When your chil
dren were young and did you and your wife ever manage to leave them so that you could go out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 
Well - to be quite frank with you - I don't know what the wife's opinion was, but my opinion was I wouldn't - leave them at all. I was too - scared you see 
- we'd big fires in those days, big open fires, you see what I mean. Well, when one of those - fire were - were got - a child was knocking about with a big poker, it was just - could - push a - a lump of coal you see and there you are, the kiddie'd be up 
in the air and it could - oh no, no, no, we never - we never left them - never left them along. That's when they were very young.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Did you ever leave them with anybody else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Did you let your children join in when grown ups were talking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 
Oh well it all depended, it all depended what they were talking about. If - after you - we'll say - we'll say now that the wife's mother came, or - or my mother came to visit us - and when the crack finished - now you two - now you children, what have
 you got to say? That - that was them in. You never got them stopped again once you got them in. But they wouldn't say anything before that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 What did you bring your children up to consider important in life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Well - what I - brought mine up to co
nsider the most important was truth. Always tell the truth. No matter what it cost you. It - it's always paid - it'll pay you, now you tell the truth.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 
Did you tell your children they should hit back when another child hit them or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Oh yes. O
h I taught them that you know, it might be - that - that was a bad thing I know. But I taught them that. Oh - you're talking about that - and - my - daughter, that was the eldest now - she had a - a kind of - she's got a career as a matter of fact, but at
 
this time it would be about seven year old, and it was at school, and there seemed to be a bully at the school. See? And - she - once or twice when I was - up she told me she says, granddad - that so and so, she's always hitting me granddad. You told me n
o
t to hit back. I didn't tell you anything of the sort, I told you to hit back if they was - wee enough. She says, well this one's no wee enough and she says, she's big. Well I says, I'll tell you what to do. Now - you'll be going to school today aren't yo
u
? And I was staying here the weekend, I'll be here 'til about Tuesday. And that girl would be going - coming out from the school to where we are, it was about a mile, she had about a mile to come from the school to here, she stayed. And - says I, now - no
w what'll happen now - that girl is starting annoying you - when she knows that your grandpa's here. And she says - and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 
Were there any other children that you discouraged your children from playing with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 No. No, no, no I never tried that, no. T
here was plenty of people did that, but I - I never just - no, I let them play in their own way. I thought that was the best way. Teach themselves to suit and that was the main thing. If you've got' to run about, they've to run about - after their mum and
 dad all the time, they'll they're no learning anything at all, they've got to learn to - do things on their own.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 If your children did something you disapproved of what would happen to them?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Oh well I gave them a good lecture. Because I always re
member what I got, I think I told you that already, it's on one of your first - sheets. That dad always said into the room, I hated that like poison, I told him, I said, I'd rather you give me a - a good hiding, dad, as - taking me into that room. Oh, oh.
 Oh I didn't like that at all, so that was how mine were taught. I - I expect they'd be the same, they didn't like this - lecture, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Did your wife ever tell them off?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Oh they - they'd no pay any attention to a woman. I - I don't think any c
hildren paid any attention to their mum, you see, but a woman's so soft. You can go up and cuddle her up and she'll - see what I mean, oh they've got the soft side of the woman
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Would you say that your children received their ideas about how to behave 
from both parents or did one of you play a more important part do you think?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16601601 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 
Well - of course the wife would have better chance than em, see she's - she's there all the time. I'm just there a few - hours a day, maybe a couple of hours a day. No, I w
ould say that they - a family - bringing up, how they are brought up - what they arrive at - that's the mother. I would say that. The poor old mum's got to take the blame. Whether she's to blame or not, because - she's the one that's bringing them up.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 When your children had a birthday was it different from any other day?
