l - after - after I - was married - I - I - I had a lot of books of my own, but - after I was married - we used to go down to Woolworths on a Saturday - and you got paperbacks, of all the classical stuff, for sixpence. You see, well - I used to get four e
v
ery Saturday. Four. Oh well - I know Dickens's works - O'Henry's works every work that you could mention. You went down every Saturday, bought somebody else's work. So they I - they - they'd plenty of reading material, I'll no say they read it all the tim
e but they - they'd plenty of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14641693 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2906979\charrsid8538783 Did you belong to a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
