 Park or Tupenglen or - Lynde Park, anywhere at all, but it was somewhere. Well - supposing you was taking we'll say - to Ruthengrlen, that appealed to them more than taking them to Ayr. It's funny that, they'd sooner a few mile away, another place miles 
a
nd miles but - some people got a kick out of these parks you see - they could do what they liked in a public park, in a - the likes of Ruthenglen and - Geln Park and all these big parks. They could - as long as they don't pull down trees, pull - pull shru
b
s or anything, they could go carrying on. Oh it was terrific, all kinds of games and everything you could play. At that time. You could play them yet as a matter of fact. So there was plenty of parks in Glasgow, you could say there were about four - about
 sixty parks in Glasgow so - you were never short of a new place. To go to.
